Standards-Version: 3.9.4.0

Package: systemback
Architecture: all
Pre-Depends: bash (>= 4.1), coreutils (>= 7.4), grep (>= 2.5.4), procps, sed (>= 4.2.1)
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, apt, dpkg (>= 1.15.5), gambas3-runtime (>= 3.5.1), ncurses-bin (>= 5.7), rsync, upstart | sysvinit (>= 2.88) | systemd
Recommends: systemback-gtk (= ${source:Version}) | systemback-qt4 (= ${source:Version})
Conflicts: live-config, live-config-systemd
Description: Simple system backup and restore application with extra features
 Systemback makes it easy to create backups of system and users
 configuration files. In case of problems you can easily restore the
 previous state of the system. There are extra features like system
 copying, system installation and Live system creation.
 .
 This package contain a command line interface and base files.

